      "span_text": "It is possible that novel sequence at the 10.8 kb deletion breakpoint may have strengthened exon 6 recognition compared to other DMD exon 5 deletions. Clearly, genomic rearrangements and the subsequent fusion of normally non-contiguous sequences can have unexpected consequences [CITATION_1] ."
